# Weekly X-Ray Auto-Enhancement Audit (2026-03-10)


## Introduction
The purpose of this document is to conduct a comprehensive self-audit of the Dental/Vertebral X-Ray diagnostic model. This assessment will focus on evaluating the model's accuracy using recent data from HuggingFace and relevant literature. We aim to propose calibration adjustments to improve structural identification, in alignment with the Forgotten Formula PMA's mission: prioritizing healing over profits and nature over synthetic solutions.


## Background
Advancements in AI and machine learning have significantly enhanced diagnostic capabilities within the realm of medical imaging. At Forgotten Formula PMA, we leverage these technologies to aid in precise diagnostics, particularly focusing on dental and vertebral health. This audit is conducted within the context of our mission to provide healing-focused solutions, devoid of corporate pharmaceutical influences.


## Methodology


### Data Sources
- **HuggingFace Models:** Accessed the latest models and datasets relevant to X-Ray diagnostics.
- **Recent Literature:** Reviewed recent academic papers and internal documents related to X-Ray enhancements and AI diagnostic accuracy.


### Evaluation Criteria
- **Accuracy:** Precision in identifying structural anomalies in dental and vertebral X-Rays.
- **Calibration Needs:** Identification of areas requiring calibration for improved clarity and accuracy.
- **Compliance with FFPMA Values:** Ensuring the model's outputs align with our healing philosophy.


